com.mobius.vdrapi.command
Class GotoCommand

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.mobius.vdrapi.command.PromptingCommandBase
        |
        +--com.mobius.vdrapi.command.GotoCommand
All Implemented Interfaces:
ICanPromptForKeyValue, ICommand, INeedFullLoginCredentials, INeedLoginCredentials, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedLoginCredentialsEx, INeedObjectWithPage, INeedObjectWithProfileLocation, INeedObjectWithSession, INeedObjectWithTraceThreshold, INeedPromptForKeyValue
public class GotoCommand
extends com.mobius.vdrapi.command.PromptingCommandBase
implements INeedObjectWithPage, INeedObjectWithSession, INeedLoginCredentials, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedLoginCredentialsEx, INeedFullLoginCredentials, INeedObjectWithProfileLocation, INeedObjectWithTraceThreshold

This command object is used to access a specified report page without having to navigate through Document Explorer. It has the following parameters:

  • DOCUMENTSERVER "xxxxxx" - this required parameter specifies the document server with which to establish a connection. If the document server needs prompting for a user ID or password, the GotoCommand makes a callback to ICanPromptForLogin.

    A document server's default trace threshold level (message logging) is set to ViewDirectSeverityLevel.SL_DISASTER, the minimum tracing level. To change the document server's trace threshold level, implement the IHasTraceThreshold interface, and assign the object to this command via setObjectWithTraceThreshold(IHasTraceThreshold traceThreshold).

  • REPORTID "xxxxxx" - this required parameter specifies the Report ID where the page is located.

  • VERSIONID "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the Report Version ID where the page is located. The required format is YYYYMMDDHHMMSS. When a version ID isn't specified, the most recent version in the report archive is used.

  • SECTIONID "xxxxx" - this required parameter specifies the Report Section ID where the page is located.

  • PAGE "xx" - this required parameter specifies the page of the section to retrieve. If its value is positive, Page represents the page number of the section specified (for example, if Page = 2, it retrieves the second page of the specified section). If the value is negative, it retrieves a page that precedes the specified section (for example, if Page = -2, it retrieves the page that is located two pages before the begining of the specified section).

Note:
  • The GotoCommand implements the INeedLoginCredentials and INeedFullLoginCredentials interfaces. However, the caller should implement either IHasLoginCredentials or IHasFullLoginCredentials, but not both. If both interfaces are implemented, the command throws a MultipleCallbacksSetException.

  • If the caller implements the IHoldSession interface, then neither IHasLoginCredentials nor IHasFullLoginCredentials is required.

execute

public void execute()
             throws CommandNotLoadedException,
                    CallbackException,
                    ViewDirectException
Executes the command that provides a session for the specified document server, (if an existing session has not already been provided), and opens an archive for the specified report and version. It then retrieves the specified page based on the input parameters. After retrieving the page data from the server, the command creates an IPage object and returns it to the caller in the ObjectWithPage callback object.

setObjectWithSession

public void setObjectWithSession(IHoldSession objectWithSession)
Sets the callback object. Under normal circumstances, the Goto command creates its own session internally, which it then uses to perform its function. This optional callback enables the caller to provide an existing session for the command to use, rather having to create its own session. When provided, the session must be connected to the document server specified in the load parameters.

Specified by:
setObjectWithSession in interface INeedObjectWithSession
Parameters:
objectWithSession - object called when this class requires a session.
